# EA AI Assistant

On-premise AI assistant for Enterprise Architects in regulated industries.

Built as a bachelor's thesis project at Czech University of Life Sciences Prague (CZU).

## Problem

Banks, insurance companies, and government institutions in the CEE region 
cannot use cloud-based AI tools (ChatGPT, Copilot) due to GDPR and 
data sovereignty requirements — but their EA teams still need AI assistance 
for documentation, gap analysis, and architectural decisions.

## Solution

A web application with a fine-tuned language model that runs fully 
on-premise inside the client's infrastructure. No data leaves the company.

## Stack
- Python
- FastAPI — backend API
- Streamlit — web interface
- Mistral 7B / LLaMA 3 — language model
- QLoRA — fine-tuning method
- ChromaDB — vector database (RAG)
- Docker — deployment

## Features
- Text generation for EA documentation
- Architectural decision support (ADR)
- Gap analysis assistance
- Context-aware responses via RAG on internal documents
- Full on-premise deployment — no cloud dependency

## Status
🚧 In active development — bachelor's thesis defense: July 2026

## Author
Ekaterina Sarycheva — CZU Prague, Faculty of Economics and Management
